{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conclusion: As AI adoption in business grows, the AI-specific attack surface expands accordingly."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt injection, training data poisoning, and model supply chain attacks are no longer theoretical risks—real incidents have been reported since 2025. What executives need to build now is a multi-layered defense posture that adds an \"AI-specific risk layer\" on top of traditional cybersecurity."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Why AI Security Is Now a C-Suite Concern"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The expansion of AI adoption is simultaneously creating "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"new targets for cyberattacks"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.gartner.com/en/newsroom/press-releases/2025-08-05-gartner-hype-cycle-identifies-top-ai-innovations-in-2025","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"Gartner"},{"type":"text","text":" positioned AI security as a critical priority in its 2025 Strategic Technology Trends, warning that the risk of enterprises facing AI-specific security incidents is rising rapidly"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"NIST AI RMF 1.0"},{"type":"text","text":" (published 2023) and the supplementary "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-generative-artificial-intelligence","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"NIST AI 600-1 Generative AI Profile"},{"type":"text","text":" (published 2024) explicitly state the need to manage AI-specific risks (adversarial attacks, data poisoning, output manipulation) separately from traditional cyber risks"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.wiz.io/blog/wiz-research-uncovers-exposed-deepseek-database-leak","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"Wiz Research (January 2025)"},{"type":"text","text":" discovered that DeepSeek's cloud infrastructure had an exposed ClickHouse database, with chat logs, API keys, and other sensitive information publicly accessible—a critical case demonstrating the vulnerability of AI companies' own security posture"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Traditional cybersecurity was built on a three-layer structure protecting \"networks, endpoints, and data.\" In the AI era, a fourth layer—"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"models, prompts, training data, and outputs\""},{"type":"text","text":"—is added. This paradigm shift is the first step required of CxOs."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. 7 Attack Vectors Targeting AI Systems"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2-1. Prompt Injection"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An attack that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"embeds malicious instructions"},{"type":"text","text":" in AI inputs (prompts). It can disable system prompts, extract confidential information, and trigger unintended behaviors. In 2025, actual incidents were reported with GPT-4o-based enterprise chatbots."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2-2. Training Data Poisoning"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An attack that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"deliberately injects false or harmful data"},{"type":"text","text":" into AI model training data. It can degrade model accuracy or steer specific outputs. Companies using open-source datasets are particularly at risk."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2-3. Model Supply Chain Attacks"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cases where models downloaded from public model repositories like Hugging Face "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"contain embedded backdoors"},{"type":"text","text":". In March 2025, approximately 100 new malicious ML models were detected on Hugging Face, with more advanced techniques including Pickle deserialization attacks confirmed ("},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://jfrog.com/blog/malicious-ml-models-found-on-hugging-face-platform/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"JFrog Security Research report, March 2025"},{"type":"text","text":")."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2-4. AI Agent Privilege Abuse"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An attack that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"exploits system access privileges"},{"type":"text","text":" granted to AI agents. When agents access databases or file systems via APIs, over-provisioned permissions become a critical risk."}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📖 For a detailed framework on AI agent privilege design—including the least privilege principle, approval flows, and audit logging—see our white paper "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.querypie.ai/features/documentation/white-paper/28/ai-agent-guardrails-governance-2026","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"\"Guardrail Design for the AI Agent Era: Part 1 – Philosophy & Design\""},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2-5. Output Manipulation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"An attack that "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"intentionally distorts AI outputs"},{"type":"text","text":". In RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) systems, techniques that manipulate AI output by altering referenced documents have been confirmed."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2-6. Model Theft and IP Leakage"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Risks include "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"reproducing model behavior through mass queries"},{"type":"text","text":" via APIs (model extraction attacks) and leakage of intellectual property from fine-tuned models."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2-7. AI-Powered Social Engineering"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cases where attackers "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"misuse AI for phishing email generation and deepfake creation"},{"type":"text","text":". Traditional social engineering attacks have become dramatically more sophisticated and harder to detect."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Lessons from the OWASP Top 10 for LLM"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://owasp.org/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"OWASP (Open Web Application Security Project)"},{"type":"text","text":" published the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"<a href=\"https://genai.owasp.org/resource/owasp-top-10-for-llm-applications-2025/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\"Top 10 for LLM Applications 2025\"</a>"},{"type":"text","text":", a critical reference standard that systematizes security risks specific to LLM applications."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Top 3 Risks and Key Countermeasures"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Prompt Injection (LLM01)"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement input validation and sanitization"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Strict separation of system prompts and external inputs"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Multi-stage output filtering"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Sensitive Information Disclosure (LLM02)"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Confidentiality classification management of training and input data"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Automated PII detection and masking"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Integration with Data Loss Prevention (DLP) tools"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Supply Chain Risks (LLM05)"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vulnerability scanning of models and libraries in use"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Verification processes for model provenance and integrity"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"AI-BOM\" management—the AI version of SBOM (Software Bill of Materials)"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. Attack Vector Comparison Table"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Attack Vector"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Risk Level"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Countermeasures"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cost"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation Difficulty"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt Injection"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"★★★★★"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Input validation, output filters, prompt separation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Training Data Poisoning"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"★★★★☆"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Data quality audits, provenance verification, anomaly detection"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model Supply Chain"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"★★★★☆"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model scanning, AI-BOM management, signature verification"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Agent Privilege Abuse"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"★★★★★"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Least privilege principle, access logs, approval gates"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Output Manipulation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"★★★☆☆"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"RAG source verification, output cross-checking"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low-Medium"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Model Theft"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"★★★☆☆"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Rate limiting, access control, monitoring"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"AI-Powered Social Engineering"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"★★★★☆"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Employee training, MFA, detection tools"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Recommended Approach:"},{"type":"text","text":" Prompt injection countermeasures and agent privilege management should be tackled as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"top priorities"},{"type":"text","text":". These two have the highest attack frequency and greatest impact."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. Building an AI Security Governance Framework"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 1: AI Asset Inventory"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Catalog all AI tools, models, and APIs in use across the organization"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Clarify "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"access permissions, data connections, and user departments"},{"type":"text","text":" for each AI asset"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conduct a Shadow AI (unauthorized AI usage) assessment"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 2: AI-Specific Risk Assessment"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conduct risk assessments based on the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://genai.owasp.org/resource/owasp-top-10-for-llm-applications-2025/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"OWASP Top 10 for LLM"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Develop "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"confidentiality-tiered usage policies"},{"type":"text","text":" for each AI asset"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Adopt a risk management framework based on the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"NIST AI RMF"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 3: Technical Countermeasure Implementation"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt injection countermeasures (input validation, output filters)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Design "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"least privilege principles"},{"type":"text","text":" and approval gates for AI agents"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Centralized AI usage logging and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"real-time anomaly detection"}]}]}]},{"type":"blockquote","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"📖 For detailed implementation procedures on approval gate design, audit log setup, and shutdown protocols, see our white paper "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.querypie.ai/features/documentation/white-paper/28/ai-agent-guardrails-governance-2026","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"\"Guardrail Design for the AI Agent Era: Part 1 – Philosophy & Design\""},{"type":"text","text":". For case studies and a 90-day roadmap, see "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.querypie.ai/features/documentation/white-paper/29/ai-agent-guardrails-governance-2026-implementation","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"Part 2: Practice & Implementation"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 4: Organizational Measures Deployment"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conduct "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"company-wide AI security training"},{"type":"text","text":" regularly (at least twice per year)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Develop AI incident response procedures"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement quarterly AI security audits"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Step 5: Continuous Improvement"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Regular collection of new attack methods and vulnerability information"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conduct Red Team exercises (simulated attacks on AI systems)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Set AI security KPIs and report to executive management"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"6. Executive Implications and Next Actions"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Takeaways"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Design AI security as an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"additional layer, not an extension"},{"type":"text","text":" of traditional cybersecurity"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompt injection and agent privilege management are the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"top priority countermeasures"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Both technical and organizational measures"},{"type":"text","text":" (training, audits, governance structure) are essential"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Specific Actions for CxOs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Today:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Check with IT/Security departments on the status of AI asset inventory"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Verify whether your AI usage policies address \"AI-specific risks\""}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"This Week:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Reference the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://genai.owasp.org/resource/owasp-top-10-for-llm-applications-2025/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"OWASP Top 10 for LLM"},{"type":"text","text":" to conduct a preliminary risk assessment of your AI environment"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Create an inventory of permissions granted to AI agents"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"This Month:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Authorize the establishment of an AI Security Officer (or AI Security Task Force)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Develop a plan for company-wide AI security training"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Consider an implementation plan for Red Team exercises"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"For Further Reading"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://genai.owasp.org/resource/owasp-top-10-for-llm-applications-2025/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"OWASP \"Top 10 for LLM Applications 2025\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"NIST \"AI Risk Management Framework 1.0\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-generative-artificial-intelligence","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"NIST AI 600-1 \"Generative AI Profile\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.meti.go.jp/shingikai/mono_info_service/ai_shakai_jisso/index.html","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"Japan METI \"AI Business Guidelines (Version 1.0, April 2024)\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://artificialintelligenceact.eu/","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"EU AI Act (Entered into force 2024, phased application from 2025)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.querypie.ai/features/documentation/white-paper/28/ai-agent-guardrails-governance-2026","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"White Paper \"Guardrail Design for the AI Agent Era: Part 1 – Philosophy & Design\""}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://www.querypie.ai/features/documentation/white-paper/29/ai-agent-guardrails-governance-2026-implementation","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":null,"title":null}}],"text":"White Paper \"Guardrail Design for the AI Agent Era: Part 2 – Practice & Implementation\""}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"AI security is not the \"brakes\" on AI adoption—it's the \"safety system.\""},{"type":"text","text":" With proper security governance, you can maximize AI benefits while managing risks. Take the first step toward countermeasures today, led by executive leadership."}]}]}